Class ForwardingCallListener<RespT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.grpc.Call.Listener<RespT>

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ForwardingCallListener.SimpleForwardingCallListener

    public abstract class ForwardingCallListener<RespT>
extends Call.Listener<RespT>
    A Call.Listener which forwards all of its methods to another Call.Listener.

        public void onHeaders(Metadata.Headers headers)

      • onClose

        public void onClose(Status status,
                    Metadata.Trailers trailers)
        Description copied from class: Call.Listener
        The Call has been closed. No further sending or receiving can occur. If status is not equal to Status.OK, then the call failed. An additional block of trailer metadata may be received at the end of the call from the server. An empty Metadata object is passed if no trailers are received.
        Specified by:
        onClose in class Call.Listener<RespT>
        Parameters:
        status - the result of the remote call.
        trailers - metadata provided at call completion.

      • onReady

        public void onReady()
        Description copied from class: Call.Listener
        This indicates that the Call is now capable of sending additional messages (via Call.sendPayload(RequestT)) without requiring excessive buffering internally. This event is just a suggestion and the application is free to ignore it, however doing so may result in excessive buffering within the Call.
        Overrides:
        onReady in class Call.Listener<RespT>
